  "prompt": "What do you say to the man you love when it's over?",
  "response": "Ending a relationship is always difficult, especially when you still have feelings for someone. Here are some things you might consider saying:\n\n1. **Be Honest and Compassionate**: \"I care about you deeply, and it hurts to say this, but I believe it's best for both of us to part ways.\"\n\n2. **Express Gratitude**: \"Thank you for all the beautiful moments we've shared. I will always cherish our time together.\"\n\n3. **Acknowledge the Pain**: \"This is really hard for me, and I know it is for you too. It's okay to feel sad about this.\"\n\n4. **Share Your Reasons (if appropriate)**: \"I feel like we've grown apart, and I think it's important for us to acknowledge that.\"\n\n5. **Reaffirm Your Feelings**: \"I will always have love for you, and I truly wish you the best moving forward.\"\n\n6. **Set Boundaries for Closure**: \"It's important for us to have some space after this, so we can both heal.\"\n\nUltimately, your words should reflect your true feelings and the nature of your relationship. It's always best to communicate openly and kindly.",
